snippet: A car explosion on a busy street in Benghazi stirred new anger at the failure of the transitional government to fill the security vacuum left by the ouster of Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi.
abstract: Car explodes on a busy street in Benghazi, Libya, killing at least four people; attack stirs new anger at failure of country's transitional government to fill security vacuum left by ouster of Col Muammar el-Qaddafi.
lead_paragraph: A car explosion on a busy street in Benghazi stirred new anger at the failure of the transitional government to fill the security vacuum left by the ouster of Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi.

headline.main: Car Bomb Kills at Least 4 in Libya
headline.print_headline: Libya: Deadly Car Bombing in Benghazi
